<dec f='dpdk_18.05/lib/librte_ethdev/rte_ethdev.h' l='2049' type='int rte_eth_xstats_get(uint16_t port_id, struct rte_eth_xstat * xstats, unsigned int n)'/>
<doc f='dpdk_18.05/lib/librte_ethdev/rte_ethdev.h' l='2027'>/**
 * Retrieve extended statistics of an Ethernet device.
 *
 * @param port_id
 *   The port identifier of the Ethernet device.
 * @param xstats
 *   A pointer to a table of structure of type *rte_eth_xstat*
 *   to be filled with device statistics ids and values: id is the
 *   index of the name string in xstats_names (see rte_eth_xstats_get_names()),
 *   and value is the statistic counter.
 *   This parameter can be set to NULL if n is 0.
 * @param n
 *   The size of the xstats array (number of elements).
 * @return
 *   - A positive value lower or equal to n: success. The return value
 *     is the number of entries filled in the stats table.
 *   - A positive value higher than n: error, the given statistics table
 *     is too small. The return value corresponds to the size that should
 *     be given to succeed. The entries in the table are not valid and
 *     shall not be used by the caller.
 *   - A negative value on error (invalid port id).
 */</doc>
